OL,3,CPeople with autism and learning
OL,4,Cdisabilities 'locked up' in hospitals
OL,6,F"This is an enduring trauma that
OL,7,Fdoesn't just stop when he goes into
OL,8,Fappropriate care. No matter how well
OL,9,Fhe's cared for now, and he is well
OL,10,Flooked after, our trauma survives and
OL,11,Fis not entirely buried."
OL,13,FDescribing what William's experience
OL,14,Fin the mental health unit was like,
OL,15,FJanis said: "He was frozen. He
OL,16,Fwouldn't move. He was like a scared
OL,17,Frabbit.
